ite is sufficiently safe for such a plan. We should postpone the question of geological disposal for at least a century and use monitored, retrievable, above-ground storage of the waste until then. Her message regarding radwaste is clear: what you can't see can hurt you.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aRadioactive waste disposal in the groundxEnvironmental aspects. 0aRadioactive waste disposal in the groundxRisk assessment. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aamerican history.  aconsent.  adue process.  aethics.  ageology.  agovernment.  ahalf life.  ahealth and safety.  alegal issues.  aliability.  amorals.  anatural history.  anatural world.  anevada.  anuclear power.  anuclear waste.  apolitical.  apolitics.  apollution.  apublic health.  aradioactive waste.  aradwaste.  arespiratory illness.  ascience.  ascientific.  aunited states history.  aus government.  aus history.  ayucca mountain.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091396740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913967423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913967/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles